divs: sighting detailstook brake from night shift at job in issaquah, wa. noted an unusually bright twinkeling star 45 degree above horizon, n to ne slowly transiting left to right moiving at about 1\4 to 1" per 5 minutes for period of 10 minutes in early dawn sky. path parallel ground. object was very brightly flashing or twinkeling much more than regular star, no other stars visible in predawn sky. went to get field glasses in car, 10x25 power. object appeared as bright white cross with long axis pointed to ground and tipped 15 degree off vertical to right. horizontal axis appeared brighter and flashing left to right, blue, green, white, orange with clockwise rotation(?). speed constant from west to east. observed 10 minutes. focus of binoculars checked multiple times against 1\2 moon to west, in case it was optical artifact, focus good, field glass propped against stable base. unsure whether object man made satellite or planet or something else entirely. the colored 'rotating lights'and odd shape struck me as curious.have not noticed a star like appearing like this before.
